Hi Ebenezer,

Thank you for the remote session!

As we spoke we checked and the Whitelist is added now. We saw that you were using an older EPP client version, we asked if you could please upgrade the EPP client to the latest version so we can see if the issue still persists. Our devs asked if with the whitelist/allowlist setup and latest EPP client the issue persists. The latest EPP client also has improved logs so if the issue still persists the logs will be more accurate.

Next steps would be:
1. Please upgrade the EPP clients.
2. After upgrading the EPP clients please check to see if the issue still reproduces.
3. If it does reproduce, please generate a new set of logs and allow the issue to reproduce itself. After that please send us the logs and we will further investigate this internally with our devs.

Best Regards,

Hi Team,

Following up from my last e-mail, the alerts continue to be few. The few that happen occur on different computers /users which are all online and are subject to those same whitelist file location settings as far as I can tell.

It would be difficult to use the test build because:

  1.  The alerts are few now.
  2.  It occurs as and when to different users which would make it hard to run on a specific computer/terminal server with some users as it may occur on others instead.

Though the alerts are now few, having them at zero would be more ideal. My question is whether the fix in the test build would be incorporated in your next EPP update which you mentioned is due somewhere in November? That way we can see if it removes all these types of alerts.

Thanks.
